# Episode seed ingestion (Human Upgrade)

Use this when the user **attaches** an episode research folder (e.g. `human_upgrade_research/markdown_output/episode-seeds/69d2bb81-1374-stemregen-drapeau/`) or asks to **seed the database** from those markdown files.

## Read the pack first

1. Open `README.md` and `00-research-summary.md` for scope and IDs (episode stub, slug, exclusions).
2. Map files to entities:

| File pattern | Entity |
| ------------ | ------ |
| `01-person-*.md` | **Person** (guests, founders, public figures) |
| `02-business-*.md` | **Business** |
| `03-products-and-chemistry.md` | **Product** + optional **Compound** |
| `04-case-studies-and-trials.md` | **CaseStudy** |

3. Follow **`@human_upgrade_research/.cursor/research_rule.mdc`** for case study ↔ business linking and GraphQL operation names.

## Recommended ingestion order

1. **People** — `createPerson` / `updatePerson` for everyone who must appear as `guestIds`, `ownerIds`, or executives, so you have stable IDs before businesses and the episode.
2. **Case studies** — `createCaseStudy` / `updateCaseStudy` as needed for material documented in `04-*`; **always** attach to the business in the same ingest flow (see research rule: `caseStudyIds` / `caseStudiesNested` on business mutations).
3. **Business** — Prefer **`createBusinessWithRelations`** or **`updateBusinessRelations`** so you can attach **owners**, **executives**, **products** (nested or IDs), and **case studies** in one coherent pass. Use **`updateBusiness`** when only scalar fields and ID arrays need changes.
4. **Products** — Prefer creating or linking via **`BusinessCreateRelationsInput.productsNested`** / relation updates when possible. If products are created separately, use **`createProduct`** with `businessId`, then **`updateBusinessRelations`** if the business must list new product IDs.
5. **Compounds (optional)** — When `03-*` lists actives/APIs relevant to catalog items, **`createCompound`** / **`updateCompound`** and attach via **`updateProductRelations`** (`compoundIds` / `compoundsNested`) on the **Product**, not only on the business.
6. **Episode (last)** — **`updateEpisode`** / **`updateEpisodeRelations`** to set **`guestIds`** and **`sponsorBusinessIds`** (and any nested guest/sponsor business payloads your API accepts), after Person and Business documents exist.

## Attachment rules (best practice)

| Relation | Prefer attaching on |
| -------- | --------------------- |
| Owners, executives, case studies, products | **Business** (`createBusinessWithRelations`, `updateBusiness`, `updateBusinessRelations`) |
| Compounds | **Product** (`updateProduct`, `updateProductRelations`) |
| Guests, sponsor businesses | **Episode** (final step: `updateEpisode` / `updateEpisodeRelations`) |

## MCP server: `humanupgrade-graphql`

The MCP server **`humanupgrade-graphql`** is the integration that exposes GraphQL tools. Use its tools (e.g. **`introspect`**, **`search`**, **`validate`**, **`execute`**) for all schema exploration and mutations/queries during ingestion—**`validate`** before **`execute`**. If the server's schema snapshot and `api/src/graphql/schema.graphql` disagree, treat the running API / repo schema as authoritative and re-introspect.
